20:49.641 --> 21:01.198
That's what John Calvin said in a quote, he says, it is certain that man never achieves a clear knowledge of himself unless he has first looked upon God's face.

21:03.561 --> 21:12.434
And then after doing so, he descends from contemplating him to scrutinizing himself, scrutinize feels like a harsh word, but that's just evaluating yourself.

21:13.026 --> 21:14.609
So it raises the question for us.

21:14.749 --> 21:21.841
If the goal is to see God so that way we can see ourselves, what will we see when we actually put our eyes upon Him?

21:22.322 --> 21:23.925
Well, that's what Psalm 139 is all about.

21:24.646 --> 21:27.531
And so we're going to take it verse by verse by verse.

21:27.931 --> 21:29.154
