A sparrow is that the cheapest offering someone could buy to give to God, meaning it is relatively valueless, and yet not one of them will fall to the ground apart from your father.

23:30.082 --> 23:31.423
He knows the smallest thing.

23:31.463 --> 23:41.094
It says in the next verse, but even the hairs of your head, they're all numbered, which for some of you isn't hard for God to count, but for others of you, you've got a lot of hair and God's really working that out.

23:41.334 --> 23:45.379
He knows all things, but it's not just that he knows all that does exist.

23:45.819 --> 23:48.602
He also knows all that will exist.

23:49.883 --> 23:55.069
I love this one, Isaiah 46, it says in verse nine, for I am God.

23:55.129 --> 23:56.631
There's no one else.

23:57.352 --> 23:58.132
I am God.

23:58.172 --> 23:59.634
There's an unlike me.

23:59.842 --> 24:04.850
declaring the end from the beginning and from ancient times, things not yet done.

