29:42.239 --> 29:43.120
Why would God do that?

29:43.240 --> 29:44.922
Why would an all-knowing God do this?

29:46.384 --> 29:47.805
So you can have confidence.

29:47.925 --> 29:52.210
So I can have confidence that God knew he was purchasing.

29:52.386 --> 30:01.840
when he died on the cross for your sins, that there's nothing about you he's ever going to uncover and think to himself, oh boy, I didn't know that was going to happen.

30:02.541 --> 30:08.090
He's never going to second guess whether or not that was a good decision calling you to salvation through faith in his son.

30:08.550 --> 30:13.278
Like he's never going to wonder, man, did I make a good call or would I take it back?

30:13.658 --> 30:16.242
No, he knows everything about you.

30:16.674 --> 30:19.238
And yet he chose to die for you anyways.

30:19.699 --> 30:22.022
He chose to rise for you anyways.

30:22.403 --> 30:26.889
That gives you, in the face of insecurity, great security.

30:27.771 --> 30:34.240
Because you can know, I am fully known, the best parts of me and the worst parts of me.

30:36.023 --> 30:39.028
And yet, I'm still fully loved.

30:39.048 --> 30:39.769
That's the first thing.

30:40.510 --> 30:41.111
Let's keep going.

30:41.231 --> 30:43.314
Second thing, we're gonna pick it up in verse seven.

30:44.642 --> 30:46.904
He says, where shall I go from your spirit?

