If I take the wings of the morning or the dawn and I dwell in the uttermost parts of the sea, even there your hands shall lead me, your right hand shall hold me.

31:04.944 --> 31:13.874
If I say surely the darkness shall cover me in the light about me be night, even the darkness is not dark to you.

31:14.562 --> 31:23.493
The night is bright as the day for darkness is as light with you.

31:23.513 --> 31:24.614
What's David saying this time?

31:25.716 --> 31:26.497
It's pretty clear, right?

31:27.398 --> 31:28.439
God's everywhere.

31:29.120 --> 31:30.862
He is everywhere.

