Now, to him, he was able to do far more abundantly than all that we ask or think.

39:27.212 --> 39:29.034
How much do you think you could ask of God?

39:30.696 --> 39:32.838
How much do you think you could think of God?

39:34.300 --> 39:35.101
He could do more.

39:35.842 --> 39:37.504
According to the power that's at work, guess where?

39:37.784 --> 39:38.625
Within you.

39:41.168 --> 39:49.216
Matthew 19, 26 says, but Jesus looked at them and he said, with man, this is impossible, but with God, all things are possible.

39:49.817 --> 39:50.738
So much so, in fact,

39:51.458 --> 39:53.761
that God is able to do even more than he actually does.

39:54.521 --> 39:55.162
Isn't that crazy?

39:55.402 --> 39:57.164
Like, he can do more than he actually does.

39:57.324 --> 40:05.453
Like, there's a story where John the Baptist, he confronts the religious leaders and he says, hey, God from these stones could raise up children for Abraham.

40:06.715 --> 40:07.836
Huh?

40:07.856 --> 40:08.316
Did he do it?

40:08.757 --> 40:09.378
Nobody could have.

40:10.559 --> 40:14.843
Exodus 32, God looks at Moses and he's like, I'm done with the nation of Israel.

40:15.084 --> 40:16.685
They've betrayed me for the last time.

40:16.926 --> 40:17.807
I'm gonna do away with all of them.

40:17.827 --> 40:18.788
I'm gonna start over with you.

40:19.929 --> 40:20.850
Could he have done that?

40:21.314 --> 40:24.679
Start over an entire nation with one man, somehow.

40:25.320 --> 40:26.902
He didn't, but he could.

40:26.962 --> 40:30.367
Again, God is all powerful.

40:30.487 --> 40:31.508
Nothing's too hard for him.

40:31.749 --> 40:34.152
He can do whatever he wants so long at a court with his character.

40:34.453 --> 40:35.594
And this is what grips David.

40:35.835 --> 40:38.558
He realizes God is not just omnipotent universally.

40:38.598 --> 40:40.141
He is omnipotent personally.

40:41.402 --> 40:48.172
And the reason he knows it is because as he looks at himself, he knows God made me exactly how he wanted me.

40:48.533 --> 40:49.554
And he made you

40:49.730 --> 40:51.272
exactly how he wanted you.

40:53.115 --> 40:54.396
Like, he didn't make a mistake.

40:55.358 --> 41:03.870
Like, wherever, wherever it is, as you evaluate yourself, whatever it is about you that you love in yourself, a great head of hair and a strong jaw.

41:03.910 --> 41:05.272
And I love the money I make.

41:06.834 --> 41:08.276
You don't get to take credit for that, bro.

41:09.598 --> 41:10.279
God did that.

41:11.660 --> 41:15.666
And even the areas of your life that you don't like what you see in the mirror.

41:16.450 --> 41:18.573
Like those things that mean you wish you could change.

41:18.933 --> 41:20.535
You've worked so hard trying to.

41:20.916 --> 41:33.712
And not even the things about your appearance, but the things in your life, the jobs you have, the cities, the city you're in, the places you go, the friends that you have, like whatever it is in terms of your station in the world, God did that too.

41:34.993 --> 41:35.975
You're not an accident.

41:36.756 --> 41:38.718
David says you form my inward parts.

41:38.758 --> 41:41.341
You knit me together in my mother's womb.

41:43.063 --> 41:45.106
Which I'm not sure if it's trending anymore,

41:45.410 --> 41:47.132
Like a year ago knitting was cool again.

41:47.192 --> 41:47.993
Y'all remember that?

41:48.053 --> 41:52.519
Like everybody was kind of in their grandma era and they were crocheting like sweaters and scarves and hats and all the sorts of things.

41:53.040 --> 41:55.823
I am, I'm no expert when it comes to knitting.

41:55.843 --> 41:57.605
I'm not a knit fluencer.

41:57.705 --> 42:02.892
And yet what I do know is every time I'd see somebody knitting or crocheting something, I love a God.

42:02.992 --> 42:04.434
It never felt like y'all finished.

42:05.135 --> 42:05.595
They're sitting there.

42:05.615 --> 42:06.156
There's always knitting.

42:06.176 --> 42:07.678
I'm like, are you ever going to wear one of these things?

42:07.958 --> 42:14.066
And yet therein was such an incredible reality about the whole science to knitting.

42:14.530 --> 42:17.294
It wasn't just that you take delight in the finished product.

42:17.534 --> 42:21.138
You took delight in the process of making whatever it was you were making.

42:23.441 --> 42:27.046
God doesn't just take delight in the person that you are.

42:27.827 --> 42:32.293
He takes great delight in the process of making you who you are.

42:32.333 --> 42:32.874
Do you see it?

42:33.434 --> 42:34.496
He knit you together.

42:34.536 --> 42:35.537
He even goes on.

42:35.797 --> 42:39.402
He says, I was intricately woven in the depths of the earth.

42:39.863 --> 42:42.546
I don't even know what that means, but that sounds awesome.

42:43.938 --> 42:47.642
which just tells you, God had a vision in mind when he made you.

42:48.023 --> 42:55.071
Like he had clarity of what he wanted to be true in your life and that he accomplished it.

42:55.872 --> 43:06.784
David even goes on, he says, in your book we're written all the days formed for me before there even was one, which tells us God only cared about who David was, but he also cared about what David did and the same thing is true for you.

43:08.486 --> 43:09.607
He has a plan for your life.

43:10.748 --> 43:12.210
He has a purpose for the way you are.

43:13.410 --> 43:16.273
That's why David said he was fearfully and wonderfully made.

43:17.295 --> 43:25.084
Like David didn't just step in front of a mirror and be like, now that is one fearful and wonderful devil.

43:25.665 --> 43:27.367
That was not the way that he looked at himself.

43:27.927 --> 43:32.713
What he thought was my God is fearsome and wonderful.

43:34.255 --> 43:39.401
And anything that bears the mark of its maker is likewise fearsome and wonderful.

43:40.883 --> 43:43.346
Augustine, he said, men,

43:43.618 --> 43:54.250
go abroad to wonder at the heights of mountains, at the huge waves of the sea, at the long courses of the rivers, at the vast compass of the ocean, at the circular motions of the stars.

43:55.892 --> 43:59.696
And yet they pass by themselves without ever wondering.

44:02.419 --> 44:12.690
You and I, we are one of the greatest evidences to the existence of God.

44:14.114 --> 44:20.561
We don't have time to get into the intricacy of the human anatomy, what it would take to make you.

44:21.422 --> 44:24.385
But I promise you, it's not by happens chance.

44:26.127 --> 44:28.750
It's not because something just fell together.

44:29.611 --> 44:32.414
It's because God, He knit you.

44:33.576 --> 44:34.497
He wove you.

44:35.238 --> 44:35.838
He made you.

44:37.140 --> 44:39.282
So if you look at yourself and all you feel is self hate,

44:40.226 --> 44:44.291
Let me be really clear, you are looking way too hard at yourself and you are not looking hard enough at your God.

44:45.332 --> 44:49.016
Because if you look at him, you will not see self-hate.

44:49.957 --> 44:51.338
You'll fall into self-forgetfulness.

44:52.179 --> 44:53.000
You'll only see him.

44:53.861 --> 44:54.622
Last one, here we go.

44:54.642 --> 45:01.870
Oh, that you would slay the wicked, oh God.

45:01.890 --> 45:04.393
Oh men of blood depart from me.

45:04.954 --> 45:08.978
They speak against you with malicious intent, your enemies, they take your name in vain.

45:09.442 --> 45:11.485
Do I not hate those who hate you, O Lord?

45:11.505 --> 45:14.149
Do I not loathe those who rise up against you?

45:14.169 --> 45:15.531
I hate them with complete hatred.

45:15.631 --> 45:16.893
I count them my enemies.

45:17.734 --> 45:18.595
Search me, O God.

45:19.056 --> 45:19.877
Know my heart.

45:20.277 --> 45:21.900
Try me and know my thoughts.

45:22.360 --> 45:26.726
See if there be any grievous way in me and lead me in the way everlasting."

45:27.427 --> 45:32.114
Now, admittedly, this last section, the fourth and final section,

45:33.282 --> 45:40.371
It doesn't read quite as smoothly or poetically as everything else did before, and it's a little bit more bristling, which begs the question for us why.

45:40.411 --> 45:45.097
Like, it seems like somebody poured salt in the open wound of David, and we need to assess why that is.

45:45.898 --> 45:46.538
Well, just think.

45:46.879 --> 45:47.660
What does David said?

45:47.700 --> 45:48.641
What is David seen?

45:48.701 --> 45:50.724
He's seen.

45:51.565 --> 45:52.926
God is omniscient.

45:53.587 --> 45:54.548
He knows everything.

45:54.829 --> 45:56.010
He knows everything about me.

45:56.511 --> 45:59.775
I'm fully known, and yet I'm fully loved.

46:01.297 --> 46:02.418
He sees.

46:02.786 --> 46:04.491
that God is omnipresent.

46:04.511 --> 46:06.898
It doesn't matter how far I try to go from God.

46:07.119 --> 46:08.944
He's with me wherever it is I am.

46:09.627 --> 46:14.802
God is omnipotent, that God cares about how I am and what I do.

46:15.586 --> 46:23.477
And because of all of this, as he thinks about all of who God is, what it loads up into his mind is gratitude for the goodness of God.

46:23.778 --> 46:32.891
He sees God, you're not just all knowing, you're not just all powerful, you're not just all, you're not just everywhere all at once, you are all good.

46:33.752 --> 46:34.834
You're so good.

46:38.800 --> 46:40.402
He's omni benevolent.

46:42.018 --> 46:45.822
which just means God is always and absolutely good.

46:46.803 --> 46:51.648
He's always good, meaning there's never a time when his goodness is not true.

46:52.869 --> 46:59.436
Some of you, you question that, but just know this book, it attests to the fact there's not a moment when he is not good.

46:59.497 --> 47:06.204
He is always good and he's absolutely good, which means everything about who he is and what he does is always worthy of approval.

47:07.265 --> 47:08.466
Luke 18, 19.

47:08.994 --> 47:10.676
Jesus said to them, why do you call me good?

47:10.836 --> 47:12.378
No one is good except God alone.

47:12.899 --> 47:18.986
Psalm 105 says, for the Lord is good, his steadfast love endures forever, his faithfulness is to all generations.

47:19.346 --> 47:23.091
Psalm 34, eight says, oh, taste and see, the Lord's good.

47:23.511 --> 47:25.314
Blessed is the man who takes refuge in him.

47:25.934 --> 47:29.979
James 17 says, every good gift and every perfect gift is from where?

47:30.179 --> 47:34.825
From above, from the only giver of a good and perfect gift, coming down from the Father of lights.

47:35.846 --> 47:38.930
You see, when we consider who God truly is,

47:39.138 --> 47:41.041
We cannot draw another conclusion.

47:41.482 --> 47:44.146
All we can arrive at is he is always and absolutely good.

47:44.587 --> 47:50.776
Like he is the most omnibenevolent being in the universe, but he is also the most omnibenevolent being to you.

47:50.817 --> 47:53.280
He's good to you.

47:53.321 --> 47:58.389
Which as I say that, I know some of you are like, how can he be good to me?

47:59.410 --> 48:02.916
Like yeah, the point is God is always good to you, but how can he be good to me?

48:03.417 --> 48:04.338
Like I've suffered

48:04.546 --> 48:05.507
I've struggled.

48:05.788 --> 48:06.849
I've strived.

48:06.970 --> 48:07.911
I feel beat up.

48:07.991 --> 48:08.893
I feel broken down.

48:08.973 --> 48:11.036
I feel bruised, Colin.

48:11.056 --> 48:12.598
This doesn't make any sense how he could be good.

48:12.638 --> 48:16.204
How can God be good and I deal with all that I've dealt with?

48:16.544 --> 48:20.690
How can God be good when bad things happen to good people?

48:28.342 --> 48:29.664
The answer to that question is they don't.

48:33.069 --> 48:33.810
For none.

48:33.986 --> 48:34.447
is good.

48:35.789 --> 48:36.329
No, not one.

48:38.252 --> 48:39.554
God alone is good.

48:40.455 --> 48:41.898
And all he does is good.

48:43.179 --> 48:49.689
And we, we are the ones who have wronged him in our trespasses and sins.

48:50.570 --> 48:58.522
And yet Titus tells us when the goodness, the goodness, and the loving kindness of God our Savior appeared, he saved us.

48:59.563 --> 49:01.426
Not because of works done by us.

49:02.978 --> 49:08.764
but according to his own mercy, by the washing of regeneration and renewal of the Holy Spirit.

49:09.906 --> 49:20.818
You see, the question that we should be conflicted with is not how can God be good when bad things happen to good people?

49:21.839 --> 49:32.050
The question we should be conflicted with is how can God be good when the worst thing happened to the best person, his own son?

49:33.058 --> 49:41.831
When I know the answer, God can be good in the face of that because it proves to us that he's so good.

49:42.712 --> 49:46.257
He does not give himself for the loveable.

49:46.958 --> 50:01.019
He gives himself for the hateful, so much so that he would offer no one else for none else is good, but he would satisfy the righteous requirement of his own wrath by laying himself down through the form of the sun.

50:01.981 --> 50:02.962
And in so doing,

50:03.170 --> 50:07.036
He would endure all the hate that you pin up for yourself.

50:07.997 --> 50:09.119
Christ died for that.

50:09.920 --> 50:17.031
He endured all the hate, all the insecurity, all the inadequacy, all the inconsistencies you feel about who you are.

50:17.112 --> 50:19.115
He endured all of it.

50:19.135 --> 50:24.523
All the hate that you have pales in comparison to all the hate God has against your sin.

50:24.563 --> 50:31.634
And yet that laid on Christ as he stood upon your cross and all the love.

50:32.066 --> 50:36.692
that you're so unwilling to give yourself, that I'm so unwilling to give myself.

50:38.975 --> 50:45.704
God has freely lavished upon us for those that have placed their faith in Him.

50:46.746 --> 50:49.029
You see, here's what you gotta know.

50:49.750 --> 50:51.372
Christ became all that were not.

50:54.216 --> 51:02.066
And so if you're here and you're insecure from what you've done, God knows all that you've done and He died for it anyways.

51:02.146 --> 51:08.973
If you're here and you're insecure from where you've been, God was there, and He's with you now.

51:09.754 --> 51:16.442
If you're insecure from how you're made, God knows what you don't like about yourself.

51:16.502 --> 51:17.523
He made it Himself.

51:18.904 --> 51:24.210
But He died to save all of you anyways, not just the parts that you think worthy.

51:24.831 --> 51:31.378
And if you're insecure from why you do what you do, why you're here, God's goodness is always

51:31.682 --> 51:35.290
reaching, especially when we're in the wrong.

51:37.715 --> 51:50.764
If you're here and you're struggling with self-hate tonight, just know you should not hate that which Christ has loved and laid his life down for.

51:50.784 --> 51:51.666
Let me pray that you wouldn't.

